From 23bd7072d2aaa9bfd21a0bceeac5dfedd242ebcb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ren Wang <iamwrm@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 23:37:47 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Support Codex multi-turn assistant history and streamed tool
 calls

Codex first turns succeeded, but later turns retried as reasoning-only:
prior assistant history was sent as easy-input messages instead of
completed output messages, and complete function calls delivered only in
response.output_item.done vanished because terminal response.output is
empty on this backend.

Normalize assistant history to pi's completed output-message shape, drop
display-only reasoning entries with empty ids, accumulate reasoning summary
deltas, and synthesize streamed function calls into both ToolCallDelta
events and the final ConversationResponse. This allows tool loops and
subsequent conversation turns to complete normally.
